review_data: Reviewed in the United States on July 27, 2021
name: Exavier Nunez
title: Delicious Yogurt - Sometimes runny
review: This is a delicious product, I get them often for my lunches to work and days out. The yogurt is very creamy and decadent with swell cultured and sweet taste. My only qualm is that when I bring it to work (often in a lunch box with an ice pack) it gets too creamy and loses its structure even after being in my lunchbox for an hour. I end up having more of a yogurt soup than a semi solid snack. Regardless, I give their flavors a 5/5, but the stability of the yogurt lacks when packed.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on June 17, 2021
name: T
title: bad
review: I've bought other flavors of this brand for years and they were good and I've always enjoyed them, mostly vanilla I think.This one smells like some kind of artificial flavoring and it's extremely pungent and disgusting.I think the actual flavor might be ok, I honestly can't tell, because I can't get past the terrible artificial smelling maple smell--it ruins the product for me.I've had other brands of maple flavor yogurt(with real syrup) and they did not have this pungent terrible fake maple smell, and neither does any real maple syrup I've ever encountered, and I've bought lots over my lifetime.The ingredients say "maple syrup" and then "natural flavor", so I don't have a clue what they've used to create this smell.Is it actually real maple syrup?Is it possible I got a bad batch?Is this "natural flavor" something added to make it pungent?I don't understand it.
